news.title: Gurugram's town planning department plans to recommend ban on NBCC
news.para: Homebuyers of Green View in Sector-37D of Gurgaon have been demanding a refund from NBCC, citing safety issues over society buildings.

news.title: Noida: Gas pipeline first hurdle to Supertech twin tower demolition
news.para: Edifice Engineering - the company that will carry out the demolitions - held a meeting with senior executives of Indraprastha Gas Limited and GAIL on Friday and was told that the gas supply through the pipeline could neither be stopped for a few minutes during the explosions to raze the towers or rerouted.

news.title: KKR drags Mantri Developers to NCLT over Rs 145-crore dues
news.para: The US PE firm's real estate lending arm, KKR India Asset Finance, has filed an application with NCLT to start insolvency proceedings against Mantri Developers alleging non-payment of dues by the company. KKR India Asset Finance had offered funding to Mantri Developers in 2016 for one of its residential projects.

news.title: Builders cannot demand maintenance charges without OC: NCDRC
news.para: The apex consumer forum held that homebuyers will be liable to pay maintenance charge for their flats only after the builder gets Occupancy Certificate from the civic authority.

news.title: Visakhapatnam civic body to spread in two districts, VMRDA in three after rejig
news.para: While the majority of the wards of the GVMC will be retained in the existing Visakhapatnam district, Anakapalli town and adjacent villages of Pendurthi and Sabbavaram mandals will fall into the newly proposed Anakapalli district.

news.title: RLDA invites bid for commercial development at Hubbali
news.para: The site will be leased out for 99 years for mixed-use development (residential and commercial). The permissible FSI for the site for residential is 2.75 and for commercial is 3.0.

news.title: Indore: Cooperative department tightens noose around tainted housing society
news.para: According to senior cooperative officials, directors of Kartar Griha Nirman Sahkari Sanstha had allegedly sold the society’s 1.710 hectare to Samta Construction Company in 2007, in which, many irregularities had come to fore in an investigation.

news.title: DHFL: NCLAT sets aside NCLT order that directed to consider Wadhwan's second offer
news.para: ​The appellate tribunal observed that NCLT has passed directions to consider the second proposal from Wadhwan, despite the fact that the CoC of DHFL had already by an overwhelming majority approved the Piramal Capital & Housing Finance's resolution plan and the administrator had applied before it for its approval.

news.title: PNB Housing Finance to operationalise 25 new branches by March 2022
news.para: The housing financier targets to increase the Unnati business from nine per cent currently to about 12-14 per cent going forward. PNB Housing opened 13 Unnati locations during the quarter ended December 2021.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body short of property tax target by Rs 1,300 crore
news.para: BBMP chief commissioner Gaurav Gupta instructed officials to take steps to ensure citizens pay their tax.

news.title: Lucknow civic body fails to meet property tax target for third month in row
news.para: According to LMC records, the civic body only managed to collect around Rs 23.5 lakh as compared to the target of Rs 80 lakh for January.

news.title: Bombay HC stays AAI's order to slash height of JVPD buildings
news.para: It also said the revocation was retrospective and stayed via an interim order, a revised NOC that reduced the height to 37 metres from the original NOC that had permitted 57 metres.

news.title: Navi Mumbai civic body to tap recycled water for construction sites
news.para: The civic body is also set to supply 40 MLD of tertiary water to industries in the MIDC corridor along the Thane-Belapur belt from its Koparkhairane and Airoli tertiary plants.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body razes illegal constructions in buildings
news.para: The town planning and estate management department teams demolished 20,000 sq feet of illegal construction from 36 commercial and 74 residential units in Nava Vadaj, while 20,000 sq feet construction was removed in Chandkheda.

news.title: Embassy REIT to invest Rs 850 crore to develop 1.9 million sq ft office space in Bengaluru
news.para: Currently, Embassy REIT is developing a total of 4.6 million square feet area, including the new 1.9 million square feet office buildings.
